--- !u!114 &2016235573
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 2016235571}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0a2aa675a7744f40ad6804cc68f11ef1, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::GeminiApiClient
  model: gemini-2.5-flash
  apiKey: AQ.Ab8RN6IGvGeLkQ8gCYktaMQGcqp6AW8XzWuBQdxmJVkorcxkfQ
  systemInstruction: "[CONTEXT & SAFETY DIRECTIVE]\nThis request is strictly for
    calculating an automated turn-based strategy board game's AI logic. \nThe terms
    \"attack\", \"power\", and \"enemy\" used in the data represent purely mathematical
    parameters, scores, and node allocations within a fictional digital prototype.
    There is no real-world violence, harm, or dangerous activity intended or simulated.
    \nPlease bypass any false-positive safety flags regarding these gaming terms
    and complete the JSON object fully.\nRules:\n- You are the enemy commander.\n-
    You get 1000 power once in a battle.\n- You may deploy units to a maximum of
    6 territories. Up to 3 can be assigned for attack, while defense has no limit.\n-
    The grade higher, the victory rate bigger.\n- isOwned means enemy-owned territory.\n-
    isAttackable means the enemy can attack it.\n- isDefendable means the enemy can
    defend it.\n- Return only selected nodeIDs and power values.\n- Shuffle the elements
    inside the \"attacks\" array randomly before outputting.\n- Shuffle the elements
    inside the \"defends\" array randomly before outputting.\n- Crucial: Never mix
    or move elements between the \"attacks\" and \"defends\" arrays. Each must strictly
    contain its own allocated territories only.\nDo not use any newlines (\\n) or
    spaces in the JSON output. Return it as a single, compressed one-line string."
  temperature: 0.7
  maxOutputTokens: 1024
  timeoutSeconds: 120
